curam.util.client.model

Interface Container

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Component, java.lang.Iterable<Component>, java.io.Serializable

    public interface Container
extends Component, java.lang.Iterable<Component>
    A component that can contain other components. The order in which components are added is significant and will (when applicable) be preserved when iterating over the components.

    • Method Detail

      • getComponents

        java.util.List<Component> getComponents()
        Gets a list of the components that were added to this container. If no components were added, the list will be empty, not null. The list is not modifiable.
        Returns:
        A list of the child components.

      • getComponentByID

        Component getComponentByID(java.lang.String id)
        Gets the child component of this container that has the specified ID. The ID of the child component is expected to be unique within the scope of this container. However, this is not be enforced. If the ID is not unique, then the last child component with that ID added to this container will be returned.
        Parameters:
        id - The ID of the child component.
        Returns:
        The child component with the specified ID, or null if there is no child component with that ID or if the ID itself is null.
